        <td bgcolor="dimgray" colspan="2" ><img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;01/02/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 20:25:43</font>

        
		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=737"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=737')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=9049&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Just+an+idea%2E%2E%2E"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I've been thinking about some of the issues with our class lately, and one thing I think still needs to be addressed is how quickly our highest level pets die.  Now, knowing Verant as I do, unless they do a complete 180 like they did with melee binds, I really don't expect them to make our pets any tougher without taking away something else from us.  So I've thought to myself, "Would I be willing to give up some ofthe damage my pets do, in exchange for a pet that lives longer?"</P><P>I've been thinking about this idea for quite some time, and never suggested it because I know there are a lot of different playstyles when it comes to the Necro, and some raid-heavy players would be terribly upset at the very mention of such an idea.</P><P>Today, the solution to this quandry occurred to me.  We CAN have our cake and eat it too.  Consider the following spell...</P><P>Ossification, level 53 Necromancer spell.  The effect is a pet buff, that reduces the amount of damage the pet does by 25%, but also reduces all damage taken by the pet by 25%  The specific details like casting time, duration, mana cost, etc. are fairly unimportant, but should be somewhat similar to our pet haste buffs.  Perhaps there even could be an upgrade to this spell that does 50% to damage done/recieved.</P><P>This way, we can tailor our pets to our specific needs at the time, and no one can whine about balance, because the trade off is even (except the mana cost).  It would be agreeable to all Necros (except the totally disagreeable ones, of course) because if you don't want to give up the extra damage output, just don't cast the spell.</P><P>Thoughts?</P><P><IMG src="http://neverquest.homestead.com/files/OurMoon/OurMoon.jpg"><BR><i>"Verant celebrates the success of their latest expansion."<i></P><P> </font></td>
      </tr>

      <tr>
        <td bgcolor="dimgray" valign="top">
        
