        <td bgcolor="dimgray" colspan="2" ><img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;01/02/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 21:13:49</font>
        
		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=471"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=471')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=73521&TOPIC_ID=9049&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Just+an+idea%2E%2E%2E&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Just a counter point. </P><P>The level 49 pet has a max of 2450HP. Lets say it has a great round hits for 55-55-55, kicks for 25, bashes for 25 for a total of 215 damage.</P><P>The level 53 has a max of 1400HP. Lets say it has a great round and hits for 57-57-57 and backstabs for 165 for a total of 336 damage.</P><P>If we took the 53 pet and cast a suggested +25%HP and -25%Damage buff on it you would have a pet that had 1750HP. On a great round it would hit for 43-43-43 and backstab for 124 for a total of 253 damage. </P><P>If we took the 53 pet and cast a suggested +50%HP and -50%Damage buff on it you would have a pet that had 2100HP. On a great round it would hit for 29-29-29 and backstab for 83 for a total of 170 damage.</P><P>Either way, the 49 pet would still own the 53 pet, really not making much of an upgrade. And that is really what everyone has trouble swallowing. Hell, with the nasty ripotse's on the higher end stuff, a lot of time the extra damage of a 53 pet is not worth the extra hassel of keeping it healthy.</P><P>I think the simple solution to allow pets to be more potent, while not giving us massive soloability is scalable pet buffs. Say a spell that gives +10%HP, +10MR, +3%Haste per group member. So in a full group, you buff your pet with augmentation then cast this second spell and your pets would get an additional +60%HP, +10MR and +18%Haste.</P><P>Hell, you could take this scalability to pretty much anything. Give us a DOT that did (1000 * number in group) of damage in under a minute. In a 6 person group a DOT that did 6000 in a minute is not abusive. A DOT that does 6000 in a minute solo is something Verant would never give us.</P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black</P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
