        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Call me dense but I'm not sure what this would truly accomplish.  If Verant makes our pets, say, 25% better (AC, HPs, Level) then using this spell would more or less become a mute point as better meaner harder hitting/tanking pets are exactly what we have all been looking for.  Using this spell would allow the pet to avoid 30% less dmg, sure, but at the same time it's now doing 30% less damage, especially detrimental on those epic level mobs where the fight stretches into minutes.  Now if you're suggesting using a spell like this in order to keep our current pets alive and possibly reduce aggro as well then the spell will have some purpose.  Even so, and this is only my opinion, I would rather skip the use of that spell and keep my 59 hitting monk pet with /taunt off and just back him off every once in awhile if occasional aggro/ripostes are dropping his health too low.  Even then, I just hit him with Pact of Shadow or Shadowbond and he does just fine.  As far as having our cake and eating it too, I seriously doubt Verant would give us better pets and actually trust us to use a spell to reduce our pet's capabilities.  I certaintly wouldn't (use the spell that is).</P><P>I'm also wondering what applications you're intending this spell for?  During solo hunting or in a group/raid situation?</P><P>Nakht Takharu<BR>56 Defiler</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
