        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Let's imagine that you increase the 56 pet's hitpoints by 25%</P><P>Then it has incrased from 1400 to 1750.  Great.</P><P>So you go to ToV on your next guild raid, and everyone buffs up getting ready to kill the next named.</P><P>And the fight begins....</P><P>You and everyone around you has just been hit by and AE for 1250 points DD.  Your pet has 500 hitpoints left versus 150 if it hadn't been buffed.</P><P>15 seconds later the next AE kills it.</P><P>Does this make a difference?  They only live through 1 round either way.</P><P>What is needed is something to make the pet have a chance of resisting an AE now and then.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
